<br>
Cherise Scarletfire<br>
lvl 17 druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DAOC Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/24/01 1:48:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divineguildpics.homestead.com/files/SalSide.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lvl 15 (epic?) Ring of Nature Affinity</span><hr size=1> Adding points does not give you new spells for the higher levels... Instead, you cast at that power level.  For example, if you have a regrowth of 10 and have +3 worth of Regrowth items, then you'll still only have the level 10 spells, but you'll cast at the power of level 13. (i.e. your heals will be stronger) <p><B>Salicia Swiftfoot<BR> 10 <I>Druid of Hibernia, Palomides Server</I><br>Proud Member of <a href=http://pub33.ezboard.com/bdaocdivine>Divine</a><br>DAoC Moderator for <a href=http://thedruidsgrove.org/>The Druids Grove</a></B><br><br> Click <a href="http://divineguildpics.homestead.com/Memorial.html"> here</a> to read the last EQ story of Salicia Swiftfoot.<BR>
